I’m back behind the mic! And with purpose - This podcast is heavily focused on mental health and deep vulnerability. The destigmatization of vulnerability in men has always been a priority for me as many of you may know 
from my previous podcast - so if your interested please give @cantaffordtherapypod a listen. 

I open up about my personal experiences with violence and it’s various forms, I share in hopes that anyone who may have experienced similar situations can find solace in not being alone…

Edit by: @co.visuals

I firmly believe that in order to know what you want and need, you need to explore and experience what life has to offer. If you limit your experiences because of fears or silly ideals of what society tells you then your missing out on learning more about yourself! 
Date, have a few friend groups, diversify your portfolio of humans and as you get older you’ll have so much insight into what makes you happiest.

What do you think? Let me know. 

Ps: @co.visuals ain’t shit for using that wide shot of me in my hoochie daddy shorts for NO REASON.

Click the link in my bio to hear more of @cantaffordtherapypod 

#podcast #mentalhealth #menshealth #dating #love

A small clip from @cantaffordtherapypod - where I share some difficulty I have with tonality, delivery & understanding the nuances of communication when it comes to things I feel passionately about. Honesty and just keeping me accountable are things that I love from my relationships - Friendships, romantic or business and because of that I often bring that energy into my relationships because that’s what I hope to be reciprocated, problem is often times because of my delivery and gruff approach I can be taken the wrong way, can be intimidating & just generally off-putting. 

  I’ve made it my business to work on this, to soften my tone & to think not only about my words but about how they sound out loud, how I can change the reception of my words with physical touch, body language, just general self awareness and a desire to become a better communicator.
 I have @ntshmrks to thank for so succinctly describing what has become a meditation phrase for me with “I need my medicine with honey” which changed the way I approach conversation both in my relationship with her and my relationships across the board.

New episode drops Wednesday wherever you get your podcasts - Please Rate, Review and subscribe and let us know what you think!

As some of you may have seen or maybe you haven’t and this post is the first time your seeing it, I was on a spectacular show called “Couples Therapy” on @showtime where Natasha and myself attended REAL couples counseling with an amazing psychotherapist named @ornaguralnik and it had a profound impact on me. I’ve seen a folks say “what would make someone want to talk about these issues on tv?” Well, let me share how that came to be for us. Me and Tash were going through some turmoil, trying to figure out our dynamic better and hitting some real roadblocks as far as communication and chemistry but we found a lot of common ground when we would watch TV shows. We would chat about how we felt about particular characters, plot lines, aesthetics etc etc…and then we came across couples therapy, we were hooked. We watched all available episodes and it made us have so many conversations about OURSELVES and our relationship and who we wanted to be for each other it was healing and we weren’t even the ones in the session!. One particularly rough day for us I laid in bed and thought about how much I wanted us to get our groove back, our paths back aligned, our passion rekindled and my mind went to the show couples therapy. Being someone who worked in Film&TV I started to look up the show and it’s producers and found an email and sent a very long email detailing my interest in the show and how it brought me and Tash together blah blah blah…anyway..so after a lengthy process we ended up here today, on a TV show talking about our relationship woe’s and doing all the better for it. It’s a weird and surreal feeling to have watched us go through therapy but it was well worth it. 
Thank you @madiganemmy @yaybennett and everyone else involved for making the process so easy and smooth.
The newest episode of @cantaffordtherapypod I talk a bit about my experience on the show and the lasting impact it made on me both as an individual and how I show up in my relationship. Thank you everyone for listening and supporting, it’s greatly appreciated.
